## **File Structure (Detailed Explanation)**  

A well-structured repository improves **maintainability, scalability, and collaboration**. Below is the **complete directory structure** for the **Exodia Terminal**.

### **Project Directory Tree**  

```plaintext
Exodia-Terminal/
│── src/                     
│   ├── scanner.js           # Main token scanner logic
│   ├── blockchainUtils.js   # Blockchain interaction utilities
│   ├── config.js            # Configuration settings (RPC URLs, constants)
│── docs/                    
│   ├── API.md               # API reference documentation
│   ├── CONTRIBUTING.md      # Contribution guidelines
│   ├── USAGE.md             # How to use the scanner
│   ├── FAQ.md               # Frequently Asked Questions
│── tests/                   
│   ├── scanner.test.js      # Jest test cases for scanner functions
│   ├── blockchainUtils.test.js # Tests for blockchain utility functions
│── .github/                 
│   ├── workflows/           
│   │   ├── test.yml         # GitHub Actions for CI/CD
│── public/                  
│   ├── images/              # Screenshots, diagrams
│   ├── logo.png             # Project logo
│── .gitignore               # Ignored files (node_modules, environment files)
│── LICENSE                  # Open-source license (MIT)
│── README.md                # Project overview and setup
│── package.json             # Project metadata, dependencies, scripts
│── package-lock.json        # Lockfile for dependencies
